ce:section.ce:para:
An electrochemical workstation (CHI760E) was tested with a conventional three-electrode system. Copper electrode, platinum electrode, and calomel electrode are used as working electrodes, counter electrodes, and reference electrodes, respectively. The open circuit potential (Eocp
                        ) test time is 2400 s. A 10 mV sinusoidal potential signal ranging from 100000 Hz to 0.01 Hz was then used to test the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS). Tafel Polarization curve was performed at a scan rate of 0.001 V s−1 in the potential range of E
                        ocp ± 0.25 V. To achieve high reproducibility, each experiment was run three times under the identical setup in a 298 K constant water bath.
